What is DataBases?
-> Its a collection of data which can be easily accessible by the authorization person

Why we prefer databases?
-> * can store large data
  * features like security & scablility etc
  * easier to insert,delete,update

Types of databases?
-> 1. SQL DB                                   2.NO-SQL DB
*It is a relational db(stored in tables)        * NOn - Relational Databases(stored in docs/key-val/graphs etc)
*ex- MYSQL , Orcale , POstgreSQL etc            * MongoDb, Cassandra, Neo4j etc

What is SQL ? 
-> SQL stands for (Structured Query language)
-> SQL is a programming language used to interact with  relational databases
 
